  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Blanch 8 ounces of water for 4 minutes, then season with namul-blanch-season.",
    "Sear the smoked salmon fillet in a pan for 2 minutes per side.",
    "Wrap each lotus leaf with a portion of the salmon, pistachio paste, avocado, scallions, and red pepper flakes.",
    "Roll up the wraps tightly, trimming excess leaf with scissors if necessary.",
    "Fry the rolls in oil for 2-3 minutes, until crispy and golden.",
    "Bake the rolls in the oven for an additional 5 minutes to melt the pistachio paste.",
    "Cut and serve immediately."
  ],
